sity of Manitoba), Cynthia Hammond (Concordia University), Kristina Huneault (Concordia University), Loren Lerner (Concordia University), Lianne McTavish (University of Alberta), Kirk Niergarth (Mount Royal University), Mary O'Connor (McMaster University), Sandra Paikowsky (Concordia University), Ruth B. Phillips (Carleton University), Jennifer Salahub (Alberta College of Art & Design), and Anne Whitelaw (Concordia University).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt, Canadian -- 19th century. 0aArt, Canadian -- 20th century. 0aArt, Canadiany19th century. 0aArt, Canadiany20th century. 0aFeminism and art -- Canada -- History. 0aFeminism and artzCanadaxHistory. 0aWomen artists -- Canada -- History. 0aWomen artistszCanadaxHistory. 7aART / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aAdams, Annmarie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnderson, Janice, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aAnderson, Janice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuis, Alena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammond, Cynthia Imogen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuneault, Kristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLerner, Loren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcTavish, Lianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiergarth, Kirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Connor, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaikowsky, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Ruth B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRacette, Sherry Farrell, econtributor.